==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thomsonianism
<hw>Thom*so"ni*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An empirical system which assumes that the human body is composed
of four elements, earth, air, fire, and water, and that vegetable
medicines alone should be used; -- from the founder, Dr. Samuel
<etsep>Thomson</etsep>, of Massachusetts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thomsonite</ent>⟦br⟧
